				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${{\rm{SWR}}}_{(100-500{\rm{cm}})}=1000\times {\rm{SWSD}}$$\end{document}SWR(100−500cm)=1000×SWSDThe total of soil water resource at the 100–500 cm soil depth across the plateau was thus quantified by summing the SWR(100–500cm) of each pixel.
